The paper deals with anti-unification in Constraint Logic Programming (CLP), which is a subfield of programming languages (cs.PL) that combines logic programming with constraint solving. The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which suggests a connection to algorithms and complexity theory (cs.AI). The concept of anti-unification involves finding a generalization that captures shared structure, which is related to the field of logic and set theory (cs.LO). The paper also involves the manipulation of sets of atoms and constraints, which suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and efficiency of the proposed algorithm, which suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
